Date: Tue, 15 Sep 1998 08:41:41 -0600 (CST)
From: Pam Wilson <Pam.Wilson@tdh.state.tx.us>

RABIES IN TEXAS - JULY 1998
During July, there were no cases of canine rabies in South Texas. To date,
no cases of canine rabies have been reported north of the South Texas Oral
Rabies Vaccination Program (ORVP) drop-zone for coyotes.
In West-Central Texas, there was one case of gray fox rabies in a fox from
Crockett County. To date, no cases of gray fox rabies have been reported
beyond the boundaries of the West-Central Texas ORVP drop-zone for gray foxes.
There were 39 cases of rabies in animals statewide, including:
26 bats*
8 skunks
3 horses
1 fox
1 raccoon
These cases were reported from the following counties:
Bexar (1 bat) Red River (1 skunk)
Comanche (1 skunk) Runnels (1 skunk)
Crockett (1 fox) San Saba (1 skunk)
Erath (1 horse) Tom Green (1 skunk)
Hopkins (1 horse) Travis (1 bat)
Kinney (1 raccoon) Upton (1 skunk)
Lamar (1 skunk) Wharton (1 bat)
McCulloch (1 horse) Williamson (23 bats)
Nolan (1 skunk)

* Of these bats, 23 were "downed" specimens collected from McNeil Bridge
in Williamson County as part of a study being conducted by the Centers for
Disease Control and Prevention.
--
Pam Wilson, RVT, MEd, CHES
Texas Department of Health - Zoonosis Control Division
Austin, Texas 78756
e-mail: Pam.Wilson@tdh.state.tx.us
